column4: I just updated to ubuntu 10.04 from ubuntu 9.10 and now my sound doesn't work. It did at first but now it doesn't at all
I just updated to ubuntu 10.04 from ubuntu 9.10 and now my sound doesn't work. It did at first but now it doesn't at all
yes I did, and nothing it muted
yes and nothing happens, I don't even get sound when I turn the computer on and log in
I suggest you load an alsa mixer like gamix and check all levels and muter. The gnome-volume-control with pulseaudio backend tend to ignore some devices
